title: Chollet conjecture
date: 2025-01-6 11:28:00-0400
description: 
permalink: /blog/conj1/
tags: inequality
categories: basics
related_posts: false
---

Let $$A$$ be a $$n\times n$$ positive semidefinite matrix. Then

$$
  per(A)^{2} \geq per(A \circ A),
$$

where $$per(A)$$ is the permanent of a matrix $$A$$, and $$\circ$$ denotes the Hadamard product.  
